# Autopus Branding Formats

> Format specifications for Autopus visual feedback and progress displays.
> These formats MUST be used by all agents as defined per subcommand context.

---

## A1: Pipeline Progress Format

Display at the start of `--team` mode and after each Phase transition in the `go` subcommand.

```
🐙 Pipeline ─────────────────────────
  ✓ Phase 1: Planning
  → Phase 2: Implementation [N/M tasks]
  ○ Phase 3: Testing
  ○ Phase 4: Review
```

**Status symbols:**
- `✓` — Phase completed successfully
- `→` — Current active phase
- `○` — Phase pending

**Rules:**
- Replace `[N/M tasks]` with actual completed/total task counts (e.g., `[3/7 tasks]`)
- Update the display after each phase transition
- Always show all 4 phases regardless of current position

---

## A2: Workflow Lifecycle Format

Display after each subcommand (plan, go, sync) completes to show position in the full cycle.

```
🐙 Workflow: {SPEC-ID}
  ✓ plan  →  ● go  →  ○ sync
```

**Status symbols:**
- `✓` — Stage completed
- `●` — Current stage (just completed)
- `○` — Stage pending

**Stage combinations:**

After `plan` completes:
```
🐙 Workflow: {SPEC-ID}
  ● plan  →  ○ go  →  ○ sync
```

After `go` completes:
```
🐙 Workflow: {SPEC-ID}
  ✓ plan  →  ● go  →  ○ sync
```

After `sync` completes:
```
🐙 Workflow: {SPEC-ID}
  ✓ plan  →  ✓ go  →  ● sync
```

